translations:
‘als
			es morgen wurde, kam der König in den Garten, um den Apfel zu
			essen’;

‘We would shake (the milk) approximately for an hour, then we
			would look into the skin: something similar to pearls has appeared
			(there)’ JL 12.14.6;

‘One piece of land that I know – people had named it the
			Hornfield. They called (it) the Hornfield. So what had happened
			there?’ LuF 304/64;

‘Muhammad, before he was born, (while he was) in his mother’s
			womb, God had written this testimony (…) about his name’ JL
			20.7.42;
